# Numly Privacy Policy

Last updated: June 11, 2026

Numly ("we", "us") respects your privacy. This policy describes what we collect and how we use it.

## What we collect

Numly does NOT collect, transmit, or sell any personal data. We do not use any third-party analytics, advertising, or tracking SDKs.

The app stores the following on your device only:
- Your game progress (stars, levels completed, best scores)
- Your settings (theme, palette, language, sound preferences)
- Your power-up inventory

This data never leaves your device unless you choose to use iCloud backup, which is managed by Apple.

## Apple services we use

Numly uses the following Apple services, which have their own privacy practices:
- Game Center — for optional leaderboards (if you enable Game Center)
- StoreKit — for optional in-app purchases (Apple handles payments)

We do not see, store, or process your Apple ID, payment information, or any personal identifiers.

## Children

Numly is rated 4+ and contains no objectionable content, no chat, no user-generated content, and no external links to other content.

## Changes

If we ever change this policy, we will update the "Last updated" date and post the new version at the same URL.

